https://leetcode.com/problems/container-with-most-water/description/

QUESTION:
Input: height = [1,8,6,2,5,4,8,3,7]
Output: 49
SOLUTION:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(1)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8    |              |
7    |  ------------|-----|  -> max area the container can have water
6    |  |           |     |
5    |  |     |     |     |
4    |  |     |  |  |     |
3    |  |     |  |  |  |  |
2    |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  
1 |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |
0 |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |

you have to keep checking at each low and high which is the lower one and multiply with the area.
max=Math.max(max,Math.min(height[low],height[high])*(high-low)); -> this is the main one.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public int maxArea(int[] height) {
        if(height==null || height.length==0)return 0;
        int low=0,high=height.length-1;
        int max=0;
        while(low<high){
            max=Math.max(max,Math.min(height[low],height[high])*(high-low));
            if(height[low]<height[high])low++;
            else high--;
        }
        return max;
    }
}
